cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper combines computer vision and natural language processing to generate novel pairs of image and text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of generative adversarial networks and sequence-to-sequence modeling, which are common techniques in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the generation of paired samples from multiple domains, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
